subtasks.details:
Create TypeScript interfaces:
- TTSAdapter { synthesizeStream(text, voice, rate, volume): AsyncIterable<TTSChunk>; supportsTimestamps: boolean }
- TTSChunk { audioBuffer: ArrayBuffer | Float32Array; timestamps?: WordTimestamp[]; isFinal: boolean }
- WordTimestamp { startMs: number; endMs: number; text: string; charStart: number; charEnd: number }
- NPCChannel { id: string; voiceId: string; queue: Utterance[]; state: 'idle'|'playing'|'paused'|'muted'; controls: { rate: number; volume: number; mute: boolean } }
- Utterance { id: string; npcId: string; text: string; voiceId: string; hashKey: string; requestMeta: { createdAt: number } }
- CaptionEvent { utteranceId: string; current: { startMs: number; endMs: number; text: string; index: number }; source: 'timestamps'|'fallback' }
Define service boundaries:
- TTSService: manages NPC channels, enqueues utterances, resolves cache, calls adapter, emits playback and caption events.
- AudioEngine: wraps AudioContext/AudioWorkletNode per channel, applies rate/volume/mute, schedules buffers.
- Cache: clip store by (text+voice hash) mapping to decoded PCM and timestamps if present.
- VoiceRegistry: NPC→voice mapping with default.
Events bus signature for UI subscription: onPlaybackStart, onPlaybackEnd, onCaptionUpdate, onControlChange.
Hashing: stable normalized key build: normalize text (NFC), collapse whitespaces, trim, lowercase optional flag, include voiceId and rate-independent; include locale if applicable.

API:
- computeCheck({baseRoll:number, modifiers:number[], dc:number, critRange?:{nat1CritFail?:boolean,nat20CritSuccess?:boolean, margin?:number}}, options?:{capTotal?:{min?:number,max?:number}}) -> {total:number, degree:'crit-fail'|'fail'|'success'|'crit-success', breakdown}
Rules: total = baseRoll + sum(modifiers). Degree: compare total vs DC with configurable margin for crit thresholds (e.g., ≥DC+10 crit success, ≤DC-10 crit fail). Natural 1/20 overrides if enabled. Provide breakdown object listing contributions. No mutation.

Data:
- Condition { id, name, stacks:boolean, maxStacks?:number, duration?:{turns?:number, expiresAt?:number}, tags:string[], effects: Effect[] }
- Effect types: {type:'modifier', value:number, scope:'check'|'skill'|'attack'|'save'} | {type:'dice-mode', mode:'adv'|'dis'} | {type:'immunity', tag:string} | {type:'restriction', ruleId}
State:
- CharacterState { conditions: AppliedCondition[] }
Pure API:
- applyCondition(state, condition, now)->state; removeCondition(state,id)->state; tick(state)->state; resolveCheckContext(state, checkInput)-> {modifiers:number[], dice:{adv?:boolean, dis?:boolean}, immunities:string[]}
Stacking policy: if stacks=false, refresh duration; if stacks=true, increment up to maxStacks and scale modifier if defined per stack.
Serialization: toJSON/fromJSON stable and versioned.

Define types:
- HookFns { getTeamModifier?(teamId:string, context:any): number, getAllianceModifier?(allianceId:string, context:any): number, adjustXp?(xp:number, context:any): number }
All rule engine public APIs accept an optional hooks:HookFns parameter and must apply these adjustments in a documented, deterministic order (team then alliance then cap). Provide no-op defaults. Ensure that serialization of context excludes functions.
